web_results.snippet: The papaya, papaw, or pawpaw is the plant species Carica papaya, one of the 21 accepted species in the genus Carica of the family Caricaceae, and also the name of its fruit. It was first domesticated in Mesoamerica, within modern-day southern Mexico and Central America.

related_questions.question: What does papaya do to your body?
related_questions.snippet: Papaya has many benefits, including protection against heart disease, reduced inflammation, aid in digestion, and boosting your immune system. There are also benefits to eating papaya seeds. You can enjoy papayas in many ways, such as in smoothies and salads.

related_questions.question: What do papayas taste like?
related_questions.snippet: What does a papaya taste like? Papaya has a sweet taste and creamy texture. Many people describe it as tasting like a cross between a cantaloupe and a mango. However, the sweetness and texture of a papaya depends on how ripe it is.

related_questions.question: Why is papaya the healthiest fruit?
related_questions.snippet: It is high in nutrients such as vitamin C, folate, vitamin A, magnesium, fiber, and antioxidants. Some of the possible benefits of papaya include anticancer effects, anti-inflammatory properties, and more. Papaya can benefit cardiovascular health, vision and eye health, hair and bone health, and more.
